237    /**
238    * Adds a value (which may be negative) to the instant value,
239    * overflowing into larger fields if necessary.
240    * <p>
241    * The value will be added to this field. If the value is too large to be
242    * added solely to this field, larger fields will increase as required.
243    * Smaller fields should be unaffected, except where the result would be
244    * an invalid value for a smaller field. In this case the smaller field is
245    * adjusted to be in range.
246    * <p>
247    * For example, in the ISO chronology:<br>
248    * 2000-08-20 add six months is 2001-02-20<br>
249    * 2000-08-20 add twenty months is 2002-04-20<br>
250    * 2000-08-20 add minus nine months is 1999-11-20<br>
251    * 2001-01-31 add one month is 2001-02-28<br>
252    * 2001-01-31 add two months is 2001-03-31<br>
253    *
254    * @param instant the milliseconds from 1970-01-01T00:00:00Z to add to
255    * @param value the value to add, in the units of the field
256    * @return the updated milliseconds
257    */

276    /**
277    * Adds a value (which may be negative) to the partial instant,
278    * throwing an exception if the maximum size of the instant is reached.
279    * <p>
280    * The value will be added to this field, overflowing into larger fields
281    * if necessary. Smaller fields should be unaffected, except where the
282    * result would be an invalid value for a smaller field. In this case the
283    * smaller field is adjusted to be in range.
284    * <p>
285    * Partial instants only contain some fields. This may result in a maximum
286    * possible value, such as TimeOfDay being limited to 23:59:59:999. If this
287    * limit is breached by the add an exception is thrown.
288    * <p>
289    * For example, in the ISO chronology:<br>
290    * 2000-08-20 add six months is 2000-02-20<br>
291    * 2000-08-20 add twenty months is 2000-04-20<br>
292    * 2000-08-20 add minus nine months is 2000-11-20<br>
293    * 2001-01-31 add one month is 2001-02-28<br>
294    * 2001-01-31 add two months is 2001-03-31<br>
295    *
296    * @param instant the partial instant
297    * @param fieldIndex the index of this field in the partial
298    * @param values the values of the partial instant which should be updated
299    * @param valueToAdd the value to add, in the units of the field
300    * @return the passed in values
301    * @throws IllegalArgumentException if the value is invalid or the maximum instant is reached
302    */

357    /**

360    * <p>
361    * The value will be added to this field, overflowing into larger fields
362    * if necessary. Smaller fields should be unaffected, except where the
363    * result would be an invalid value for a smaller field. In this case the
364    * smaller field is adjusted to be in range.
365    * <p>
366    * Partial instants only contain some fields. This may result in a maximum
367    * possible value, such as TimeOfDay normally being limited to 23:59:59:999.
368    * If this limit is reached by the addition, this method will wrap back to
369    * 00:00:00.000. In fact, you would generally only use this method for
370    * classes that have a limitation such as this.
371    * <p>
372    * For example, in the ISO chronology:<br>
373    * 10:20:30 add 20 minutes is 10:40:30<br>
